reviewText: It's nothing more then a kids verison of Encino Man. The only good thing about this film is animation got better. The story is very unoriginal and gets detailed by pointless filler moments that slow the movie. The subplot is barely notable. It's sad that the only people in this film that I can stand are Jugman & Reggie's Robot. You have to sink pretty low to make them tolerable by comparison. It's bland,it's tried and it's dumb. I give this film a 1 out of 10. P.S. I'll only watch it because of B & V. wink wink.

reviewText: Retaining the atmosphere "Archie's Weird Mysteries" has, "The Archies in Jugman" is a nice little follow-up to the PAX cartoon.Most of the original voice cast is present, and the animation style is the same. Many of you may not like the film, but it's meant to be a "B" movie.
